# DavidOS environment variables
#
# The core app needs NO environment variables. The app is fully local-first.
# NEVER commit a real .env file. NEVER put secrets in source code.

# --- Optional today: Google Drive backup export (v0.3 foundation) ---
# The gated "Export backup to Drive" button in Settings only activates when
# this is set. It is a PUBLIC OAuth web client ID (not a secret), but keep
# your real one out of the repo anyway — put it in a gitignored .env.
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# Google OAuth client secret must NEVER live in a frontend bundle.
# Static PWA integrations use Google Identity Services browser authorization.
# Short-lived access tokens stay in memory only; no refresh token or client
# secret belongs in the app bundle.

# --- Future: AI providers ---
# API keys must NOT be baked into the PWA bundle. Options when we get there:
#   1. Paste-at-runtime key stored only in-memory or in local storage with a warning
#   2. A tiny personal proxy the user controls
# VITE_AI_PROXY_URL=

# --- Future: GitHub ---
# VITE_GITHUB_APP_CLIENT_ID=
